   Saint Georges Georges Blanc

Restaurant Le Pré Aux Clercs à Dijon

   Le Pré aux Clercs, a major restaurant in Dijon since 1863, offers a
   stunning view over the most beautiful square in the town and
   perpetuates a certain idea of gastronomic pleasure as a precious aspect
   of life. Still loyal to the spirit of Georges Blanc’s brasseries, the
   menu of Le Pré aux Clercs restaurant invites us to rediscover the
   signature dishes of a delicious, reassuring and warming cuisine. The
   cleverly redesigned space offers a place that is both welcoming and
   intimate, where modernity joins forces harmoniously with a tradition
   that is jealously preserved.
   More Book your table Set Menu
   facebook
   assiette
   Le pré aux Clercs

Hotel Les Maritonnes Parc et Vignoble
in Romanèche-Thorins

   Dating back to the 19^th century, the old farm of Les Maritonnes Parc
   et Vignoble has been fully refurbished. It is nestled in the heart of
   Beaujolais, in Saône et Loire, country of famous Moulin à Vent wines.
   Just 15 minutes from Mâcon, 35 minutes from Lyon and 50 minutes from
   Beaune…
   More Book your stay
   facebook instagram tripadvisor
   Hôtel Les Maritonnes Georges Blanc

Hotel Château d'Igé
in Saône-et-Loire
since 2017

   Located in the heart of the Mäconnais wine-growing region, in southern
   Burgundy. The Château d'Igé offers you 10 rooms and 7 suites,
   tastefully renovated when it was taken over by Georges Blanc Group.
   Housed in a 13th century castle, Château d’Igé is a haven of peace and
   greenery.
   More Book your stay
